Package shapes

Class Rectangle

  • java.lang.Object
    • shapes.Rectangle
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Shape
    class Rectangle
extends java.lang.Object
implements Shape
    This is the rectangle class, it will be one of the three shapes used to demonstrate polymorphism.

    It will directly implement the shape interface and will define the methods associated with it.

    A rectangle is created using 2 parameters, Length and Height.

    Author:
    Dalton

    • Constructor Detail

      • Rectangle

        public Rectangle​(int l,
                 int h)
        The non-default constructor for a Rectangle object.

        It takes two parameters, length and height.

        NOTE: This constructor initializes area and perimeter using the given length and height.

        Parameters:
        l - Parameter for the (int) length of the rectangle
        h - Parameter for the (int) height of the rectangle
